# Auto-push to GitHub

Remote: https://github.com/leniumcapital/daily-brief.git

After making any code, config, or docs changes in this project:

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to review what changed.
2. Stage all relevant files (never commit `.env`, secrets, or `node_modules`).
3. Commit with a clear message describing the why.
4. Push to `origin main` immediately: `git push origin main`

Do this at the end of every task without waiting for the user to ask again.

If push is rejected, pull with rebase first (`git pull --rebase origin main`), resolve conflicts, then push.

If git is not initialized, set up the repo and add the remote above before pushing.
